  "biography_html": "<div class=\"research-section\">\n<p class=\"research-text\">Sclerias the Tragedian was a 4th-century BCE dramatist. No biographical details for him survive, and his name does not appear in major reference works such as the Oxford Research Encyclopedia of Classics, Smith&#x27;s Dictionary, or the Encyclopædia Britannica.</p>\n<p class=\"research-text\">He is associated with a single, untitled work. No extant text or specific citation is recorded, indicating the work is lost and known only by name or from fragmentary transmission.</p>\n<p class=\"research-text\">His absence from standard biographical dictionaries suggests Sclerias was a minor or obscure figure in Greek tragedy, possibly recorded only in a lost ancient list of dramatists. His literary influence cannot be determined.</p>\n</div>",
